### Create a new Ground Truth Definition
POST https://localhost:5001/api/groundtruth/definitions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userQuery": "How to troubleshoot login issues?",
  "userId": "user123@example.com"
}

### Add an entry to a ground truth definition (replace {id} with actual ID from create response)
POST https://localhost:5001/api/groundtruth/definitions/{id}/entries
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "response": "Check password reset options and verify account status",
  "requiredValuesJson": "{\"issue_type\": \"login\", \"priority\": \"high\"}",
  "rawDataJson": "{\"user_id\": \"user123\", \"timestamp\": \"2025-09-13T11:52:00Z\"}"
}

### Update validation status (replace {id} with actual ID)
PUT https://localhost:5001/api/groundtruth/definitions/{id}/validation-status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "validationStatus": "Pending",
  "userId": "validator456@example.com"
}

### Get a specific definition (replace {id} with actual ID)
GET https://localhost:5001/api/groundtruth/definitions/{id}

### Get all ground truth definitions
GET http://localhost:5105/api/GroundTruth/definitions

